Favorite lunch place, and not just mine! Expect a long but fast moving queue at lunchtime.  Delicious chicken shwarma (can choose from different proteins including vegetarian options), health choice of grains, such as freekeh, or greens, and a long list of tasty add-ons, hummus, baba ghanoush, pickles, cabbage, olives, and more!

We ordered through Grubhub on 02/06 and 07/2020 for our client meetings. They have  delicious lebanese cuisine, excellent customer service, great prices, well-balanced and variety in their menu and Grubhub delivery is on point! We will continue to cater our guests and business meetings with this restaurant. Thank you Naya #3!

Nice Mediterranean counter-service place in  the basement of 1 NY Plaza. Delicious food,  and very economic. The bowl pictured was $12. You customize your own pita, bowl or salad, choosing between 5 different bases and 4 proteins and 2 vegetarian options. You then add as many as you want from almost 20 toppings, and like 5 dressings or sauces. The food is surprisingly tasty and fresh. After 4 PM the place is empty. One star less because the seatings are a little uncomfortable for me. Worth visiting on repeat.
I order delivery from here at least 3x/week. I love the falafel & the bowls, and the fattouch is surprisingly authentic
Great food and generous portions but be sure to order ahead through their website at lunch time or be prepared to wait on a line that puts Trader Joe’s to shame
Good fresh food and fast service, always has a line for a reason, (much longer on rainy/cold days)
Big portions and food is well seasoned. I'm always happy when I come here for lunch, even though the line can get pretty long.
Good food, fast service and affordable spot!

The best Mediterranean food in the City! Fast food at its finest. Definitely the definition of NY. And they have the best Baklava.
Delicious mediterranean food at fantastic price. Very fast and fabulous service.
If I stay late at work, I order from this place.  The food is delicious, they always get the order right and the delivery time is short.
No one beats this place for middle eastern food in FiDi. Considerably large portions, great taste and very quick service.

My favorite place to go quick Mediterranean eats! It's similar to Chipotle in the sense that you can choose what you want, but you can choose all of the toppings at no extra cost. The line usually extends out the door, but don't worry! It goes by relatively quickly.  Definitely get as many toppings as you can! They really make the meal worth it. I don't ask for olives or any of the spicy sauces on my bowl, but you can ask for the sauces on the side when you pay. Always say yes to the pita because why not? The bowls I order are around $11 and I would consider it a good price because they give you a lot of food. I typically eat my meal from Naya for lunch and dinner. Overall, highly recommend!

Food 5, value 5, service 5, comfort 4 - too noisy and too tight, but guys your lunch stop is the best pick in this plaza. You have hard-working stuff and the idea with cashless checkout is genius on many levels. Honestly, I would invest.

Ordered a shish taouk. Great topping selection. One of the food prepares was not trained properly luckily for me he did not fold my pita as person before me would have had a challenge eating his sandwich. I did not have an that issue great taste and value servers were very polite
The friendliest staff in the world. Genuinely great people who make great food. Shout out to Maria, Miguel and all the awesome people who work here.
Omg! <3

Delicious, filling meal filled with flavor. First time visitor and definitely a returning customer.

Late to the game. I finally tried NAYA for the first time last week after almost a year of working in the area. Yummy yummy! I got a NAYA roll chicken shawarma with all the fixings except feta, jalapenos, and the green sauce (wanted to keep it simple, haha). Next time, I will ask for more red sauce, and maybe try the green sauce too. It's a good portion for the price. Quick service--I went around 3 pm.  So glad I am finally in the game.

A favorite place for quality middle eastern food. Visited Sat afternoon. I will be back with my relatives.
Decent food and you get a lot.

Did not like.  I ordered the Naya Bowl with Freeka, with white sauce, chicken, lettuce. Did not like the taste, rather bitter. I think it had lemon. The lines are long but run quick. They do not take cash, only debit/credit. I also ordered appetizer sampler which added another $3 plus to the bill. Not good. Two pieces of falafel that were small and hard (outside trucks do a way better job), the little mini pie which was sour (lemon), the Rekakat which tasted alright but deep fried, and a pastry which tasted good, but again, fried. Just not happy with any of it. This is a case where the idea to go to a restaurant because of the long lines does not pan out. But if you enjoy sour, fried food, go for it.
You may see a long queue but they process orders very quickly. I loved having chicken shawarma bowls here, they were absolutely delicious and the quantity is a lot!
Really good and healthy mediterranean food
Good food. Would’ve like a little more flavor but very enjoyable for a quick lunch

I ordered a Naya bowl ($11+) with rice, vermicelli and chicken shish kebab. Toppings included hummus, garlic whip, diced tomatoes, pickled red cabbage, onion salad and pickled onions. The order also comes with pita bread. The food is fresh and very delicious. The food tastes more like a marriage between chipotle and Mediterranean food.  The portion size was good, it could be 2 meal portions for someone like me. It’s usually crowded and long lines during work week, but it’s worth the wait. Make sure you’re ready with your order because the line moves fast.
My go to for take out and pick up. The food is always fresh and delicious, and the service is always on point! xo, Christina from NST Pictures
Middle Eastern Chipotle/Qdoba.  Good and filling.  Be ready with your order.
Great Mideterian food for reasonable prices
Great value, freshly made Lebanese food. Quick service and has seating.
Recommended Mediterranean food

All these good reviews must be coming from people who dont know what real Lebanese food tastes like otherwise they would barely have 1 star. I couldn't believe my eyes when I saw the (very hard couple day old) bite size spinach pies that they charge over $1 for. And the bread is not freshly made neither is the sandwich. It didnt come with the specific ingredients I asked for it was just the standard falafel sandwich which I can tell was sitting there for a while considering the bread was extremely soggy. I called to speak to the manager and he couldn't understand a word I was saying without me having to repeat myself 5 times. They will never get my business again
Had delivery, everything was fresh and delicious especially their fresh pressed watermelon juice.
Food was good. The line was out the door, but it moved fast

It used to be one of my favorite middle eastern food places in NYC. I don’t know what happened, maybe change of manager?  cook? Menu? I don’t know, but the fact of the matter is that the food quality is not that great anymore. I’m sad 😞

For weeks I have been looking for chicken shawarma in NYC financial district and thank god I found NAYA. It’s hidden in the underground food court of One New York Plaza. It’s fast food assembly line style like Qdoba or Roti and it’s as good as those guys. If you like Chicken Shawarma you have to give it a try. The special tasty rice and chicken shawarma combination is just so good.
This place is awesome! My Friend and I drive in from Brooklyn once a week to eat lunch here.
Falafel sandwich is the best !
Amazing mediterranean fare for a fair price. Ask for extra garlic paste.

Naya is a solid fast casual middle eastern/Mediterranean restaurant with a varierty of meat and vegetarian options. Most of the time the meats are cooked and seasoned well but I've had instances of dry chicken shwarma. The garlic sauce is a must have as well as the babaganoush. I really enjoy the vermicilli rice they offer as well. It has a butteryness to it that is unlike anything I've had. Overall, the food is tasty and healthy and I continue to come here over and over if I want a delicious, quick, healthy meal that isn't just the usual boring salad.
(Translated by Google) EXCELLENT CUSTOMER SERVICE.  (Original) EXELENTE ATENCIÓN AL CLIENTE.

I come here about once a week. Good food and good service. Always willing to accommodate wishes like more lettuce, less rice etc. Last week my card got charged twice for one meal, it was resolved super quickly by the cashier. It can get busy but the line moves very fast.

This place has really good value for your money and it's packed with flavor. They pile on the ingredients and as long as you aren't picky you can get quite an array! I think the tray I walked out with weighed about two pounds. The Chicken Shish Taouk was real good and the garlic whip is so potent that I almost wanna dislike it but I can't and instead think it's amazing just like everyone else. I'll definitely be back.

One of my favorite lunch places in the area.  Recommend the chicken shawarma in a roll with everything on it.  The big up over Chipotle's burritos is that Naya rolls are grilled, which helps keep them from falling apart- a subtle but substantial advantage.
The food is amazing. It's pretty much high end Halal food but man do you get a bang for your buck! 5 stars for sure!
